                            <h3>Access to safe water and sanitation gives kids time and health for school</h3>
                            <p>When children don’t have access to water at home, they are often responsible for
                                collecting it for their families. Sharing the burden with their mothers, children around
                                the world spend 200 million hours each day collecting water. This takes time away from
                                school. Likewise, poor sanitation keeps kids, especially girls, from being able to go to
                                school.</p>
