                        <div class="rich-text">
                            <h3>The water crisis impacts girls around the world</h3>
                            <p>Girls who lack access to safe water and sanitation at home or at school face significant
                                challenges. Compounded by the fact that their safety and health are at risk when they
                                have no choice but to defecate in the open, menstruation poses another reason why girls
                                in impoverished, water-insecure communities do not go to school. Access to water and
                                sanitation changes this. If for instance in India, water and toilets were accessible to
                                even 1% more girls in secondary school, the country&#x27;s GDP would rise more than $5
                                billion. Further, on a global scale, for every year a girl stays in school, her income
                                can increase by 15-25%.</p>
